<div class="admin-view">
  <h3>Workflow <small>Edit</small></h3>

  <form>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label class="control-label" for="name">Name</label>
      <input type="textbox" name="name" id="name" value="" class="form-control"  placeholder="Enter a workflow name" required />
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label class="control-label" for="turn_around_days">Turn around time</label>
      <input type="number" name="turn_around_days" id="turn_around_days" class="form-control" min="0" step="1"/>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-danger">
      <div class="panel-heading"><h3>Caution!</h3></div>
      <p>Changing these options on an existing workflow is not recommended and can have unpredictable effects.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Enabling reporting will cause <strong>all</strong>strong> existing assets to appear in the reportable page.</li>
        <li>Enabling reporting will also distort turn around times for the initial set of assets.</li>
        <li>Disabling comments can cause loss of existing comments if a batch is edited.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons">
      <label class="btn btn-primary" for="hasComment">
        <input type="checkbox" autocomplete="off" name="hasComment" id="hasComment"> Has comment
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-unchecked"></span><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-check"></span>
      </label>
      <label class="btn btn-primary" for="reportable">
        <input type="checkbox" autocomplete="off" name="reportable" id="reportable"> Reportable
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-unchecked"></span><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-check"></span>
      </label>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>
